PN,30902
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F309A1780617775
OL,3,CThe secret mission to transport the
OL,4,CBayeux Tapestry to the UK from France
OL,6,FThe piece illustrates the Battle of
OL,7,FHastings, where William the Conqueror
OL,8,Ffought King Harold to become the first
OL,9,FNorman king of England.
OL,11,FSubscribe free to our weekly
OL,12,Fnewsletter for exclusive and original
OL,13,Fcoverage from ITV News. Direct to your
OL,14,Finbox every Friday morning.
OL,16,FIt has been displayed in the Bayeux
OL,17,FTapestry Museum in Bayeux, Normandy,
OL,18,Fsince 1983, but will be rehomed in the
OL,19,FBritish Museum until 2027 while the
OL,20,FFrench site undergoes renovation.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/17
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,310,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30903
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F309A1780617775
OL,3,CThe secret mission to transport the
OL,4,CBayeux Tapestry to the UK from France
OL,6,FThe delicate tapestry's journey to
OL,7,FBritain has raised concerns over its
OL,8,Fsafety, with some historians and
OL,9,Fexperts considering the trip too much
OL,10,Fof a risk. But the British Museum has
OL,11,Fassured the public that efficient
OL,12,Fpreparations have been made.
OL,14,FHere's everything you need to know.
OL,16,FWho made the tapestry and what is its
OL,17,Fsignificance?
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/17
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,310,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30904
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F309A1780617775
OL,3,CThe secret mission to transport the
OL,4,CBayeux Tapestry to the UK from France
OL,6,FThe Bayeux Tapestry is the only
OL,7,Fsurviving depiction of the 1066 Norman
OL,8,FConquest, making it one of the world's
OL,9,Fmost famous pieces of Medieval art.
OL,11,FDespite its name, it is actually an
OL,12,Fembroidery, made of dyed wool stitched
OL,13,Fonto a bleached linen background
OL,14,Ffabric.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/17
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,310,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30905
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F309A1780617775
OL,3,CThe secret mission to transport the
OL,4,CBayeux Tapestry to the UK from France
OL,6,FThe tapestry is thought to have been
OL,7,Fstitched by a team of Anglo-Saxon
OL,8,Fwomen within a few years of 1066.
OL,9,FWilliam the Conqueror's brother,
OL,10,FBishop Odo of Bayeux, is also believed
OL,11,Fto have been involved, as he is
OL,12,Ffeatured several times in the piece.
OL,14,FThe pictures in the tapestry - some
OL,15,Fgraphic and gory - tell the story of
OL,16,FHarold accepting the crown from King
OL,17,FEdward. In response, William, who
OL,18,Fthought the English crown was rightly
OL,19,Fhis, crossed the Channel with an army
OL,20,Fand fought Harold to the death in the
OL,21,FBattle of Hastings.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/17
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,310,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30906
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F309A1780617775
OL,3,CThe secret mission to transport the
OL,4,CBayeux Tapestry to the UK from France
OL,6,FIt includes the famous image of King
OL,7,FHarold being killed with an arrow
OL,8,Fthrough the eye, although historians
OL,9,Fbelieve this may have been a late
OL,10,Faddition to the embroidery.
OL,12,FThe piece has been classified as a
OL,13,FHistoric Monument since 1840, and was
OL,14,Flisted in the UNESCO "Memory of the
OL,15,FWorld" Register in 2007.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/17
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,310,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30907
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F309A1780617775
OL,3,CThe secret mission to transport the
OL,4,CBayeux Tapestry to the UK from France
OL,6,F"It has survived events that could
OL,7,Fhave led to its destruction, such as
OL,8,Fthe Wars of Religion, the French
OL,9,FRevolution, and the Second World War,"
OL,10,Fsaid Philippe Belaval, the French
OL,11,Fspecial envoy for the loan of the
OL,12,Ftapestry to the British Museum.
OL,14,F"It is therefore an extremely precious
OL,15,Fobject in every respect."
OL,17,FHow is the Bayeux Tapestry travelling
OL,18,Fto the UK?
OL,26,@rD@Prr
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/17
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,310,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30908
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F309A1780617775
OL,3,CThe secret mission to transport the
OL,4,CBayeux Tapestry to the UK from France
OL,6,FThe tapestry will make its way to
OL,7,FLondon in a shock-proof container
OL,8,Fspecially designed to cushion
OL,9,Fvibrations, France's culture minister
OL,10,Fsaid during a Paris press conference
OL,11,Fon Wednesday.
OL,13,FThe journey has already had two
OL,14,Frigorous trial runs, and the crate
OL,15,Fthat the artefact will travel inside
OL,16,Fcan absorb 96% of the forces it
OL,17,Fencounters, according to a study by
OL,18,Fthe French culture ministry.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/17
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,310,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30909
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F309A1780617775
OL,3,CThe secret mission to transport the
OL,4,CBayeux Tapestry to the UK from France
OL,6,F"Never in the history of transporting
OL,7,Fworks of art have so many tests, so
OL,8,Fmany protocols, so many risk checks
OL,9,Fbeen carried out for a single
OL,10,Frelocation," Catherine Pegard said,
OL,11,Flikening the container to a "cradle in
OL,12,Fwhich a newborn has been laid".
OL,14,FIt will be taken by train through the
OL,15,FChannel Tunnel at night, accompanied
OL,16,Fby a police escort.
OL,26,@nD@AOUrD@LO]rD@Yrr
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G9/17
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,310,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30910
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F309A1780617775
OL,3,CThe secret mission to transport the
OL,4,CBayeux Tapestry to the UK from France
OL,6,FLight, dust, changes in temperature,
OL,7,Finsects and mould all endanger the
OL,8,Fpreservation of cloth, according to
OL,9,Fthe British Museum, and it was kept
OL,10,Fbetween 18 and 20C, with a level of
OL,11,Fhumidity at around 50%, in France.
OL,13,FWhat do critics of the journey say?
OL,15,FMultiple experts in France have
OL,16,Fopposed moving the tapestry due to its
OL,17,Ffragile state, with a 2020 report made
OL,18,Fby eight antique textile restorers
OL,19,Fstating that "no vibration-absorption
OL,20,Fsystem currently exists" to ensure
OL,21,Fzero risk during transportation.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G10/17
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,310,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30911
SC,0011
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F309A1780617775
OL,3,CThe secret mission to transport the
OL,4,CBayeux Tapestry to the UK from France
OL,6,FA petition against the move, launched
OL,7,Fby French art historian Didier Rykner
OL,8,Flast year, has more than 78,000
OL,9,Fsignatures.
OL,11,FPainter David Hockney, who wrote a
OL,12,Fbook on art's famous masterpieces,
OL,13,Fdescribed the tapestry as "too
OL,14,Fprecious to take a risk with".
OL,16,F"Rolling, unrolling, or hanging it in
OL,17,Fa new way can cause tearing, stitch
OL,18,Floss and distortion of the fabric.
OL,19,FUneven tension is causing structural
OL,20,Fstrain," Hockney wrote in The
OL,21,FIndependent.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G11/17
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,310,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30912
SC,0012
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F309A1780617775
OL,3,CThe secret mission to transport the
OL,4,CBayeux Tapestry to the UK from France
OL,6,F"Even minor mishandling could cause
OL,7,Firreversible damage. It has survived
OL,8,Fso far like a miracle, being hidden
OL,9,Faway for 300 years until it was
OL,10,Fdisplayed permanently in the 1800s."
OL,12,FWhat do others say?
OL,14,FPrime Minister Keir Starmer and French
OL,15,FPresident Emmanuel Macron have both
OL,16,Fhailed the tapestry's UK display as a
OL,17,Flandmark cultural exchange which
OL,18,Fcelebrates the long-standing
OL,19,Frelationship between the two countries.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G12/17
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,310,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30913
SC,0013
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F309A1780617775
OL,3,CThe secret mission to transport the
OL,4,CBayeux Tapestry to the UK from France
OL,6,FIts display will mark the 1,000th
OL,7,Fanniversary of the birth of William
OL,8,Fthe Conqueror, the French nobleman who
OL,9,Fled the conquest.
OL,11,F"It is so powerful a piece of art that
OL,12,FI think the more people who can see
OL,13,Fit, the better," medievalist Professor
OL,14,FGeorge Garnett told ITV News.
OL,16,F"It will, of course, generate great
OL,17,Finterest in the Conquest."
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G13/17
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,310,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30914
SC,0014
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F309A1780617775
OL,3,CThe secret mission to transport the
OL,4,CBayeux Tapestry to the UK from France
OL,6,FThe British Museum told ITV News the
OL,7,Ftapestry is not yet in the UK and
OL,8,Femphasised they were not able to share
OL,9,Fany further details on its security
OL,10,Fmeasures.
OL,12,F"The British Museum has a world-
OL,13,Fleading conservation and collections
OL,14,Fmanagement team who are experienced at
OL,15,Fhandling and caring for this type of
OL,16,Fmaterial," a spokesperson said.
OL,18,F"There is a strong collaborative
OL,19,Fspirit between France and the UK and
OL,20,Fteams are working closely on the
OL,21,FTapestry's upcoming display."
OL,26,@}D@]O]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G14/17
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,310,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30915
SC,0015
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F309A1780617775
OL,3,CThe secret mission to transport the
OL,4,CBayeux Tapestry to the UK from France
OL,6,FHow long will the tapestry be on
OL,7,Fdisplay?
OL,9,FThe exhibition will begin in
OL,10,FSeptember, with tickets for the first
OL,11,Ffour months available from July 1.
OL,13,FTwo further ticket releases will be
OL,14,Fmade in October and January for access
OL,15,Fbetween January and March, and April
OL,16,Fto July 2027.
OL,18,FWhat will happen to the tapestry after
OL,19,Fthe British Museum exhibition?
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G15/17
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,310,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30916
SC,0016
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F309A1780617775
OL,3,CThe secret mission to transport the
OL,4,CBayeux Tapestry to the UK from France
OL,6,FThe artefact will be returned to
OL,7,FFrance once the Bayeux Tapestry Museum
OL,8,Fis restored.
OL,10,F"We will return the tapestry safe and
OL,11,Fsound after the exhibition, on time,"
OL,12,FLord Peter Ricketts, UK envoy for the
OL,13,FBayeux Tapestry loan said during the
OL,14,Fpress conference.
OL,16,F"Yes, maybe we are the 'perfidious
OL,17,FAlbion', but not to that extent," he
OL,18,Fjoked, referring to the historical
OL,19,Fterm used to describe England's past
OL,20,Fbetrayal of France.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G16/17
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
